Brazil, microcephaly. 5 May 2016. (susp.) as of 30 Apr 2016, 3580 cases, (conf.) 1271 cases; deaths 57 cases [stillbirths? Neonates?]
http://www.latercera.com/noticia/tendencias/2016/05/659-679401-9-brasil-confirma-casi-1300-casos-de-microcefalia-vinculados-a-zika.shtml [in Spanish]

Colombia (Santander and Norte de Santander departments). 29 Apr 2016. (reported) as of 19 Mar 2016, 11 515 cases; 5 municipalities with high incidence (more than 1000 cases per 100 000 population).
Ref: Rodriguez-Morales AJ, Haque U, Ball JD, et al: Spatial distribution of Zika virus infection in northeastern Colombia [submitted]. Bull World Health Organ E-pub: 29 Apr 2016. doi: 10.2471/BLT.16.1765

Peru. 3 May 2016. (reported) 3 locally acquired cases, 2 from Yurimaguas in Loreto region and one from Jaen in Cajamarca region.
http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2016/05/peru-finds-local-zika-cases-report-supports-complication-links

Venezuela. 1 May 2016. (reported by the Venezuelan Society for Public Health), 2978 pregnant women suspected of having had Zika virus infections; microcephaly, 1 case suspected in Sucre state. Public education programs inadequate.
http://www.el-nacional.com/sociedad/Sucre-nacio-primer-microcefalia-vincula_0_843515716.html [in Spanish]

